      "description": "Presenting a collector-grade 1994 Mazda RX-7 FD, a masterclass in lightweight engineering and rotary performance. This example features the iconic 1.3L 13B-REW sequential twin-turbocharged powerplant, delivering linear boost across the rev range with surgical precision. The chassis remains incredibly rigid, benefiting from a front-midship engine placement and a perfect 50/50 weight distribution. Mechanically pristine, the forced induction system holds peak pressure without deviation, and the five-speed manual gearbox offers crisp, short-throw engagement. The Torsen limited-slip differential ensures optimal power delivery through the rear wheels. Meticulously maintained with verified compression numbers and a flawless exterior, this FD represents a rare opportunity to own a pure, analog driving machine in its most refined state.",
